name: The League of Legendary Ladies, Pack One
description:
The first pack in a series of cards that trades on knowledge about black women (some famous, others not) who have been trailblazers for and at the forefronts of their chosen fields.

The front of each 3.5 x  2 inch card contains an image, while the back contains a brief biography. 

This introductory pack of cards includes Shirley Chisholm, Katherine Dunham, Marian Anderson, Althea Gibson and Nella Larsen

name: Pin-Up Postcard
description: This group of beautiful black women from the 1940's illustrates the timelessness and endurance of black womanhood. Grab 'em before they sell out!

name: In The Army Now Postcard
description:
Black women have served our country, even when we were constitutionally defined as being less than our white counterparts. We always have and always will be integral to the fabric of the United States.

Grab 'em while you can!
